The paper discusses the challenges of using multiple modeling languages in the development of complex software systems, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also discusses concrete language composition artifacts, approaches, and mechanisms, which are related to programming languages (cs.PL) and logic (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper focuses on the coordination of multiple languages, which is related to software design (cs.SD) and distributed systems (cs.DL).
